cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper is about learning visual representations using self-supervised learning, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new approach to organizing and reasoning data with multiple variations, which involves using a graph with millions of objects (cs.LG). The paper uses a Triplet-Siamese network with VGG16 as the base architecture, which is a common approach in deep learning (cs.AI). The paper also applies the learned representations to different recognition tasks, such as object detection and surface normal estimation, which are common tasks in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
